6 AS INTRODUCED
7 A Concurrent Resolution declaring May 14, 2025, as
the 9th annual Hispanic Cultural Day in Oklahoma;
8 recognizing the Hispanic community in Oklahoma; and
celebrating the heritage, culture, and contributions
9 of Hispanics to the State of Oklahoma.
10
11
12 WHEREAS, Hispanics are those who identify their origin as the
13 heritage, nationality group, lineage, or country of their birth or
14 that of their parents or ancestors before their arrival into the
15 United States; and
16 WHEREAS, Spanish-speaking countries include Argentina, Bolivia,
17 Chile, Colombia, Costa Rica, Cuba, Dominican Republic, Ecuador, El
18 Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, México, Nicaragua, Panamá, Paraguay,
19 Perú, Spain, Uruguay, Venezuela, and the Commonwealth of Puerto
20 Rico; and
21 WHEREAS, Hispanics have been a part of the geography and history
22 of Oklahoma since the 16th Century when the Spanish initially
23 claimed Oklahoma, specifically the Oklahoma Panhandle; and
